value.0: This bed has a beaten straw mattress, lined with well worn cotton sheets and covered with a worn woolen blanket.  Tended quite well, washed and scented, you will not find any bedbugs living here.  Soft enough to allow even the most hard adventurer a decent nights rest.

Trika was a potent, yet sweet wine made in Calimshan. It was considered a luxury and made for an excellent gift.
Garlic is well known as a herb for flavoring foods and treating heat stroke among the preasantry. It is also used to repulse vampires.
This was a lime in water, which most considered to be rather refreshing on hot days.
This is a drop of sweet molasses.
This bucket seems like it could hold enough water to douse a fire or properly rouse a sleeping person.
